'''毒品戰爭'''，是[[美國|美國]]主要政治術語<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.npr.org/2016/03/27/472023148/legalize-all-drugs-the-risks-are-tremendous-without-defining-the-problem |title=存档副本 |access-date=2017-05-05 |archive-date=2017-05-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170512114404/http://www.npr.org/2016/03/27/472023148/legalize-all-drugs-the-risks-are-tremendous-without-defining-the-problem |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>"(And) Richard Nixon was the one who coined the phrase, 'war on drugs.'"</ref>，常用於表示[[美國聯邦政府|美國聯邦政府]]對於[[毒品|毒品]]的防制而做出的行动，即{{Link-en|軍事支援|military aid}}、[[入侵|軍事干預]]、減少{{Link-en|非法藥品交易|Illegal drug trade}}。<ref name="whiteout-chapter-14">Cockburn and St. Clair, 1998: Chapter 14</ref><ref name="Bullington 1990 39–55">{{Cite journal|last = Bullington |first = Bruce |author2=Alan A. Block  |date=March 1990 |title =  A Trojan horse: Anti-communism and the war on drugs |url = https://archive.org/details/sim_crime-law-and-social-change_1990-03_14_1/page/39 |journal = Crime, Law and Social Change |volume = 14 |issue = 1 |pages = 39–55 |publisher = Springer Netherlands |issn = 1573-0751 |doi = 10.1007/BF00728225 }}</ref>

這一舉措包括一套旨在阻止違法生產，分配和消費的藥物政策對於[[精神药物|精神药物]]的政策並且參與政府[[联合国|联合国]]的對策。這個詞在1971年6月18日由[[美国总统|美国总统]][[理查德·尼克松|理查德·尼克松]]發表的新聞發布會不久之後普及—尼克松總統出版了尼克松總統給藥物濫用預防和控制大會的一個特別信息， 宣布吸毒為“第一公敵”。他向國會發出的這個消息包括關於將更多的聯邦資源用於“預防新的吸毒者和康復上癮者”的文本，但這部分並不像“毒品戰爭”一樣受到公眾的重視。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.presidency.ucsb.edu/ws/?pid=3048|title=Richard Nixon: Special Message to the Congress on Drug Abuse Prevention and Control.|publisher=|accessdate=2017-05-05|archive-date=2013-12-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131212201341/http://www.presidency.ucsb.edu/ws/?pid=3048|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Nixon Calls War on Drugs">{{cite news|title=Nixon Calls War on Drugs|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=-5IjAAAAIBAJ&sjid=RLcFAAAAIBAJ&pg=973,31915&dq=nixon+war+on+drugs&hl=en|accessdate=2012-10-13|newspaper=The Palm Beach Post|date=1971-06-18|archive-date=2015-10-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151012234718/https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=-5IjAAAAIBAJ&sjid=RLcFAAAAIBAJ&pg=973,31915&dq=nixon+war+on+drugs&hl=en|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Dufton|first=Emily|title=The War on Drugs: How President Nixon Tied Addiction to Crime|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/health/archive/2012/03/the-war-on-drugs-how-president-nixon-tied-addiction-to-crime/254319/|accessdate=2012-10-13|newspaper=The Atlantic|date=2012-03-26|archive-date=2012-11-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121105093614/http://www.theatlantic.com/health/archive/2012/03/the-war-on-drugs-how-president-nixon-tied-addiction-to-crime/254319/|dead-url=no}}</ref>不過，在此之前兩年，尼克松已經正式宣布了“毒品戰爭”，旨在消除、阻截、監禁。<ref>Payan, Tony (2013). A War that Can’t Be Won. Tucson, AZ: The University of Arizona Press.</ref>

毒品戰爭可能確實起到了減少藥物濫用的效果，在美國，毒品戰爭使得使用[[非法藥物|非法藥物]]的總人數下降了至少40%，根據一項受到[[美國衛生及公共服務部|美國衛生及公共服務部]]贊助的研究，在1979年，美國總共有兩千五百萬人使用非法藥物；而在1999年，則有一千四百八十萬人使用非法藥物。<ref>{{cite web |author1=National Institute on Drug Abuse |title=Fact Sheet - Substance Abuse - A National Challenge Prevention, Treatment and Research at HHS |url=https://archives.drugabuse.gov/news-events/news-releases/2000/12/fact-sheet-substance-abuse-national-challenge-prevention-treatment-research-hhs |website=National Institute on Drug Abuse |publisher=National Institute on Drug Abuse |access-date=2021-02-26 |archive-date=2021-03-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210319001311/https://archives.drugabuse.gov/news-events/news-releases/2000/12/fact-sheet-substance-abuse-national-challenge-prevention-treatment-research-hhs |dead-url=no }}</ref>

主張結束“毒品戰爭”的[[非營利組織|非營利組織]]{{Link-en|Drug Policy Alliance|Drug Policy Alliance}}估計美國每年為這些舉措花費510億美元。<ref>{{cite web|title=Drug War Statistics|url=http://www.drugpolicy.org/drug-war-statistics|publisher=Drug Policy Alliance|accessdate=2014-02-25|archive-date=2017-07-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170705125711/http://www.drugpolicy.org/drug-war-statistics|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref>On May 13, 2009, [[Gil_Kerlikowske|Gil Kerlikowske]]—the Director of the [[Office_of_National_Drug_Control_Policy|Office of National Drug Control Policy]] (ONDCP)—signaled that the [[Presidency_of_Barack_Obama|Obama administration]] did not plan to significantly alter drug enforcement policy, but also that the administration would not use the term "War on Drugs", because Kerlikowske considers the term to be "counter-productive".</ref>
<ref name="WSJCZAR">{{Cite news|title=White House Czar Calls for End to 'War on Drugs'|url=https://online.wsj.com/article/SB124225891527617397.html|work=The Wall Street Journal|date=2009-05-14|accessdate=2009-05-14|first=Gary|last=Fields|archive-date=2013-08-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130822170303/http://online.wsj.com/article/SB124225891527617397.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>ONDCP's view is that "drug addiction is a disease that can be successfully prevented and treated... making drugs more available will make it harder to keep our communities healthy and safe".</ref><ref name="dup2"/><ref>One of the alternatives that Kerlikowske has showcased is the [[drug_policy_of_Sweden|drug policy of Sweden]], which seeks to balance public health concerns with opposition to [[drug_legalization|drug legalization]]. The prevalence rates for [[可卡因|可卡因]] use in Sweden are barely one-fifth of those in Spain, the biggest consumer of the drug.</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.thelocal.se/20140410/swedens-strict-anti-drug-laws | title=Sweden's tough drug laws leave addicts behind | work=[[The_Local|The Local]] | date=2014-04-10 | accessdate=2014-09-10 | archive-date=2020-12-19 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201219075023/http://www.thelocal.se/20140410/swedens-strict-anti-drug-laws | dead-url=no }}</ref>2011年6月， {{Link-en|全球藥物政策委員會|Global Commission on Drug Policy}}發表了關於毒品戰爭的批評性報告，報告中宣稱：“全球毒品戰爭已經失敗，對世界各地的個人和社會造成破壞性後果。[[麻醉品单一公约|麻醉品单一公约]]開始五十年後，尼克松總統發表美國政府毒品戰爭後的幾年，迫切需要國家和全球藥物管制政策的基本改革。”<ref>{{cite book|title=War on Drugs|year=2011|publisher=The Global Commission on Drug Policy|page=24|url=http://www.scribd.com/fullscreen/56924096?access_key=key-xoixompyejnky70a9mq|access-date=2017-05-05|archive-date=2021-04-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210410234037/http://www.scribd.com/fullscreen/56924096?access_key=key-xoixompyejnky70a9mq|dead-url=no}}</ref>該報告被反對藥物普遍合法化的組織所批評。<ref name="dup2">[http://www.ibhinc.org/pdfs/IBHCommentaryonGlobalCommissionReport71211.pdf Global Commission on Drug Policy Offers Reckless, Vague Drug Legalization Proposal, Institute for Behavior and Health, Inc, July 12, 2011] {{Wayback|url=http://www.ibhinc.org/pdfs/IBHCommentaryonGlobalCommissionReport71211.pdf |date=20110726165232 }}. (PDF).</ref>

